ives coalescing around four core concerns: the quality of education, cultural identity, inequality of opportunities and questions of justice and democracy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEducation, HigherzEurope. 0aEducation. 0aEnglish languagezEurope. 0aLanguage and educationzEurope. 0aLanguage policyzEurope. 4aEnglish. 4aEurope. 4aHigher education, tertiary education. 4aLanguage Studies. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 4aSociolinguistics. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aEDUCATION / Bilingual Education.2bisacsh  aEnglishization, identity, quality, higher education, lingua franca, comparative studies.1 aBelyaeva, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCierpich-Kozieł, Agnieszka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDannerer, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimova, Slobodanka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrljača Margić, Branka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGabriels, René, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGabriëls, René, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaisch, Martina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGustafsson, Magnus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHultgren, Anna Kristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunter, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKling, Joyce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relato